> Adding a little pinch more of this or a dash more of that is the difference between a good dish and a great dish, so take time to work out what flavours are missing and adjust your seasoning to taste. The flavours in tonight's recipe are fresh, zesty and light so make sure you don't overpower them by adding too much salt or pepper - slowly does it!

Trim off any small leaves from the @fennel{1} and keep to one side. Cut the fennel in half lengthways through the root, remove the triangular root, then very thinly slice. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @echalion shallot{1} into half moons. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Zest the @lemon{½}, then cut in half. Halve the @red chilli{½} lengthways, deseed and finely chop. Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{10} (stalks and all).

Put a large #saucepan{} of @water{} with a pinch of @salt{pinch} on to boil for the pasta. Heat a splash of @oil{splash} in another large saucepan over medium-high heat. Add the sliced fennel and shallot and cook until softened, stirring frequently, ~{7-8%minutes}. Add the garlic, cook for ~{1%minute} more, then add the water (see ingredients for amount). Bring to the boil, then remove from the heat.

Add the @spaghetti{200} to your pan of boiling water and cook for ~{11%minutes}. When cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pan with a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} to stop it sticking together. In the meantime, shell the @pistachios{25}, then roughly chop.

When the pasta has ~{5%minutes} cooking time left, reheat the fennel mixture over medium heat. Add the @baby spinach{125}, stir through and cook until wilted, ~{3%minutes}. Stir in the @ricotta cheese{200}, lemon zest and season with @salt and @ground black pepper{}. Warm through (do not boil!), then remove from the heat. Taste and add lemon juice and red chilli to your liking.

Add the drained pasta to the sauce along with the parsley and three-quarters of the @hard Italian style cheese{40%g grated}. Taste again and add more chilli, lemon juice and salt and pepper if it needs it.

> Seasoning is key in this dish, so taste, season with salt and pepper and taste again.

Mix together the @balsamic vinegar{12} and @olive oil{1} and drizzle over the watercress, tossing to combine. Serve the pasta in deep #bowls{} with a sprinkling of remaining hard Italian cheese and the pistachios. Top with the fennel leaves and serve with the @pea shoots{40} and baby leaf salad. Dig in!